Dr. Tasto and his team of technicians and staff are top notch. They have always made my experience of visiting the dentist enjoyable. During my regular maintenance visits for teeth cleaning and x-rays, I am guaranteed to be treated professionally while enjoying a positive atmosphere. I have been told more than once during my teeth cleanings that Dr. Tasto has created a work environment that his staff are happy and proud to be a part of.

Nobody likes to have to pay for additional dental work, and the professionals at Dr.Tasto's understand this. Xrays by Kassandra were effortless, gentle and efficient and she was a lovely addition to the the consultation process, and the most amazing meet with Dr. Tasto sealed the appointment for me, he was the most caring, comprehensive and informative dentist I have ever had. Highly advanced knowledge in all area of dental and implant issues, listens to concerns and educates patient with queries, a truly top notch dentist to whom I will trust All my dental issues with in the coming months into years.  I felt an immediate trust, and felt Dr. Tasto heard all my concerns, understands medical issues I have,  and has the highest knowledge to address this to ensure my experience in his office will be of the highest quality!!! Best experience ever!!!<//Text>

<Date>1553996017336<//Date><gmapID>0x80dbf91c38e90c81:0x251c6a6c05efc112< /gmapID><Pictures>None</Pictures>< Text>
Everybody at Scripps West Dental is the best.  I've been a patient for maybe over 10+ years and I always feel like family every time I visit.  Dr. Tasto is my dentist and he is very friendly. He thoroughly explains what's going on with my teeth.  When he sees potential issue, he explains what should be done, but not forcing me to make the decision on the spot, rather he keeps an eye on it and he informs me with the condition everytime I visit. Monica is my hygienist. She is really good at what she does.  She listens to my concerns and she addresses them if she can, or she provides advice what I should do to prevent it get worst. She then explains it to Dr. Tasto so he can evaluate it.  She is the one who inspired me to floss my teeth every day, which really helped to keep my teeth healthy.  The staffs in front office are friendlier as ever.  I highly recommend this dental clinic..</Text>

I hadn't had a facial in years but a friend told me about this great place on Union St. So I booked an appointment for a Human Extractor facial. It was a great experience. I walked in to what looked like an apartment turned spa. It was clean and simple. The facial was great, but a bit painful. Let's just say she got everything out! It was what I hoped for. I broke out a bit the following week (research showed me that was normal, esp since it had been so long since I had one). The week after that my skin was clear and glowing. I definitely recommend this place. I may try a peel the next time. If it's been a while since you've had a facial, don't do it right before a big event, in case you break out like I did.< /review>

< text>
I hate leaving bad reviews, but there are so many glowing ones for Modvellum, I felt people needed a balance perspective.

I get facials regularly.  I was on a quest to find the place for me after a move.  This place was not it. The facial room was cold and there was no sink in the facial room.  It is not hygienic to have someone handling skin be unable to wash their hands after extractions.

The facial itself was very superficial.  There were very few extractions.  The girl went light on the products and barely did a massage.  I was left under the mask for a very long time, not because it needed to be on that long to be effective, but because it allowed the esthetician to be out of the room.

I know I got this facial on a deal, but I think of offers from merchants as a acquisition cost per new client: they give me a deal on a great service to get me in the door and then make back the money they lost on the deal by gaining a regular customer.

In this case, their quality of the service I had was terrible and I would never pay full price or even the discounted price for a repeat.  Modvellum will never make a regular customer out of me.<//text>

<gmapID>0x808580c2ce0c2ead:0xbcb6e335956e0009<//gmapID><text>1st time I visited Modvellum (with a deal), I saw Daria and I loved my experience. We did a facial the first time and then on my next couple of times, we did a light peel in addition to my facial to help with scars. She was super friendly and she made me feel comfortable talking about product. The first time I purchased a "100% Pure" face wash that I really enjoyed, and the 2nd time or 3rd time, I purchased a "Cosmedix" Serum to help with cell turnover. It really worked!

My next time to Modvellum, I saw Olga. Olga strongly suggested an intense peel instead of my facial. She made me feel like I was making the wrong decision by sticking with the facial instead of the peel. I was worried about peeling at work during the following  days from a more intense peel. Even if I was wrong to not do the peel instead of the facial, I don't feel like clients should feel uncomfortable at any time during their service for any reason. In light of that, I feel confident in my decision as I am a licensed cosmetologist. Unfortunately, a day or so after my facial my nose was SO sore from the extractions. I was unimpressed. Went in for a facial that I bought from a Groupon thinking that it would be a nice way to relax. My appointment started about 15-20 minutes late so I sat and waited for a while since I showed up 10 minutes early to be sure I got the full time. The woman who gave my facial was very judgmental of my skin! When she asked what I used and I responded with "Olay," she quickly said "Is that due to budget?" in an unfriendly tone. When I confessed that I wasn't good at sticking to my regimen, she said "yeah, I can tell." I was shocked! I mean, my skin isn't perfect but it's FAR from bad! <text>My wife, daughter and I tried this place for the first time today and enjoyed it. The menu offers a good variety of dishes including; Tacos, Burritos (dry and wet), Tortas, Sopes, Flautas, Nachos, Enchiladas, Menudo (Sat. & Sun. Only), Chiliquelas and more. My Daughter ordered the Nachos and was dissapointed that they were made with shredded cheese instead of traditional nacho cheese. They were also topped with sour cream and guacamole, and were pretty tasty overall. We ended up ordering our daughter a chicken sope to offset her disappointment, which she really liked. My wife orderd a Torta Cubana, which she enjoyed for the most part but was kinda thrown off by the addition of hot dog wiener. I ordered tacos con papas, which was served with rice and beans; I had no complaints. The prices are reasonable, ranging from 5 to 9 dollars depending on the dish. I Give Karina's Tacos a 4 out of five. It isn't the best Taco joint I have visited, but this place got the job done.<//text><date>1537678352859<//date>< rate>

<review>This place is so ghetto that I've seen brighter, cleaner and more professional medical offices in the crumbling parts of eastern Europe, back when any country there was referred to as being part of a 'bloc.'

She then proceeded to imply that I never called their office in the first place - that I had called corporate and had been misinformed. Either way, someone there dropped the ball on me because now I could not see anyone and had to reschedule. The same receptionist then suggested that I see one of the doctors as an out-of-network option, and that I could pay out of pocket for such things as exam, cleaning and x-rays. Really?! <user_name>Dyvamarye<//user_name>< review>
Extracting my wisdom teeth was way less painful than having my tongue pierced. The procedure took at most 15 minutes, 10-13 for the local anesthesia to set in then two minutes extracting my two wisdom teeth. I was in such disbelief and shock that my teeth have even been removed until Dr. Webb showed them to me because I felt nothing but slight pressure. It was quick, easy and painless and I have yet to feel any pain several hours later, Dr. Webb and his staff made me feel super comfortable and all around super professional! I would definitely recommend him!</review>

This guy truly loves what he does. I went in to have what I thought was only one wisdom tooth removed, and I quickly learned that there was all 4. When he came into the office, the whole room shifted. He brings joy to hard situations and gives you this feeling of everything is going to work out.. and it did, way more than I could have even hoped for. Dr. Webb noticed I had a lisp and took a look at my tongue and noticed I was tongue tied! Without even a second thought, he just said "Let's do both surgeries at once!" He made the whole process actually enjoyable, which is really difficult to do with oral surgery. I can't recommend this guy (and his amazing staff) enough. Please don't hesitate or look any further for your oral or cosmetic surgery, this is your guy!< /text>

My wife and I had dinner at the new Alcapulco Restaurant in Alameda last week. It was perfect. We were long time customers of the old Alcapulco and weren't certain we would like the new Alcapulco. We do.

<rate>5<//rate>< review>
I have been going to stones pet shop for a few years now and I have literally nothing but good things to say.
1. They will order things in for you if they dont have it.
2. They will adjust prices if other places are selling for a lot cheaper.
3. The workers are super nice and knowledgeable on different topics. They are also honest when they dont know something. They wont just make up stuff (experienced this a lot at other places)
4. The owner is super helpful and involved in his store.
5. One of the best places in monterey to get aquarium necessities ordered. They add up a bunch of peoples orders to meet requirements for whole sale orders, then order them all from whole sale. They also dont mark up the fish too much. Theyll give you a call so you can be there when the whole saler drops off the fish, so theres less stress on the fish.</review>

<review>First off, the reason I rated the "Appeal" as "Very Good" instead of excellent is because this is not a couture pet boutique that you might find in Carmel. Instead, it is manned by very friendly and knowledgeable people who can give you educated advice ranging from what food you should give your hamster to fitting your dog for a harness (see other review). They also have a couple of groomers on board now, and I've heard that they are very good.

Anyway, their little space is crammed with high-quality pet diets & products. They sell crickets too. If you don't see what you want, you can ask the staff and they will often check their storage area or make a special order for you. Realize that Stone's carries predominantly pet PRODUCTS and does not sell animals (...although I think that they have some birds for sale?). It's a great place.

Highly recommended.</review>< pics>

<Review>So my wife & I are always looking for a fantastic authentic American BBQ joint which is almost impossible to find these days. Well we've located our haven in C J's BBQ & Fish. The service was fantastic, the 2 gentlemen who worked there were very pleasant & the food was out of this world. I ordered the 2-way & chose pork ribs & chicken with mild sauce which comes with 2 sides as well (we both ordered fries & BBQ baked beans) for $21. My wife ordered the small catfish nuggets which was $14. Now I know the prices may seem high to some (who don't usually frequent BBQ establishments) but it's really not considering we both had enough left over for an entire 2nd meal. I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone who is in search of authentic high quality food. Next time we go we plan to try the peach cobbler & some cake. (Oh & almost forgot, we also ordered 3 hushpuppies for $1 & they were extraordinary as well. We were extremely pleased).<//Review>< pictures>

<user>112612393907503073675<//user>< name>
David Armstrong<//name>
<time>1464132856894<//time><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
I see that a lot of people seem to have had bad experiences with this company.  For what it is worth, I have been familiar with them for nearly 10 years, and have been impressed with their service.

My first experience with Web (now WASH) was in a small, 8 unit apartment in Long Beach.  I only had to call for repair once, and a technician was out the next day to fix it.  The only 'negative' about that experience was that they listed my contact number as the maintenance number for the property, so I got a couple of calls from them when a technician was dispatched and needed to be let in.  I explained to them that I was a tenant and they took my number out of their system.

I have called them half a dozen times since moving to a large apartment complex (over 100 units) here in Costa Mesa.  Every time they have dispatched a technician who has fixed the problem in less than 48 hours.  That might sound like a big deal, but each of the laundry rooms here has 3 washers and 3 dryers.  While having one unit down is a drag, it is not a show stopper.

They have an 800 number so all calls are free.  They put asset tags on all of their machines so they know exactly what machine you are calling about when you call.

The only negative that I would put down for them is that their card / cash machines are SUPER sensitive.  I suppose I understand because they want to cut down on fraud, but it gets frustrating when the machine spits out perfectly good, brand new, crisp clean bills.  It would be nice if they could dial down the sensitivity on the bill readers just a little bit.</Text>

<Date>1517269494587<//Date><user_name>Melanie Cotrich< /user_name>< Review>
WASH provides the washing and drying machines at my college dorm, and I've never had a problem using them. The washing machines have load sizes options and water temperature options, so you can wash your delicate clothing in cold water if you don't want them to shrink. It usually takes less than half an hour to wash your clothes. The drying machines have the same type of settings, even letting you dry your clothes in low heat, but it can take longer than an hour if you do so. Like I said, I've never had a problem with machines not working correctly, or my clothes needing more time in either the washer or driver. One cycle has always been enough. Overall, WASH offers an easy to understand product that covers all your needs.<//Review>

We hope that the issues with your machines have been resolved, but if not please let us know.'}< /Resp>

<user_name>Kevin Dorst<//user_name><date>1531331656266< /date><rating>5< /rating>< text>
I live within the city limits of San Diego. Just over the years ago, the city removed the leftovers of a building that they tore down 12 years ago (about time, right?). The problem was that mice and rats had moved into the piles of wood and other stuff. When they cleared out the piles, the mice and rats moved into the houses closest to the piles. I was a block away, but was over-run. In less than two months, I had over $22,000 in damage. They are the electrical wires, two sofas, all of the ducts for hearing and air. Orkin (I already had a monthly service contract) was at my house every day (sometimes multiple times a day) until the problem was solved. They did a great job and worked long hours. I continue with the monthly service, but if I see, hear or suspect that I might have a rat or mouse, they respond (usually within two hours) to help me out. I recommend their service and know that if you have a pest problem, they will work to correct the problem.</text>
